- Clone the Repository -
git clone https://github.com/your-username/your-repository.git

- Pulling Changes from an Existing Repository -
# If you have already cloned the repository and want to update it with the latest changes
cd your-repository
git pull 

- Downloading a Single File -
# If you want to download just a single file instead of the entire repository, you can use curl or wget
curl -O https://raw.githubusercontent.com/your-username/your-repository/branch-name/path/to/your-file.txt
or
wget https://raw.githubusercontent.com/your-username/your-repository/branch-name/path/to/your-file.txt

- To clone the repository -
git clone https://github.com/johndoe/i3-config.git

- To download just the file using curl -
curl -O https://raw.githubusercontent.com/johndoe/i3-config/main/i3-commands.txt
or
wget https://raw.githubusercontent.com/johndoe/i3-config/main/i3-commands.txt
